## Brand review: CAP homepage variants K1 / K2 / K3

### Why it feels generic
- **Audience gaps:** `K1` and `K2` still talk to a broad “người học / phụ huynh” bucket instead of clearly choosing who the hero is for first. `K3` is better because it names `Học tiếng Pháp`, `Du học Pháp`, and `Cho phụ huynh`, but even there the hero still stays broad instead of choosing one sharp first tension. See [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:43), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:75), [variant-k3.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k3.astro:181).
- **Copy genericness:** `K2` is the worst offender. It is full of agency/presentation/meta wording: “Một homepage đậm hình ảnh hơn”, “Phần này là điểm neo của K2”, “page này thiên về hình ảnh hơn”. That is not brand copy; that is design-review copy. `K1` also leaks meta language like “homepage phải cho thấy” and “Một homepage tốt...”. See [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:69), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:188), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:227), [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:86), [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:195).
- **Hierarchy failures:** All three routes use the same template hero: soft gradient field, big headline, dual CTA, stat cards, big polished mentor image, then more rounded cards. That is template hero behavior, not route-specific decision flow. See [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:35), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:59), [variant-k3.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k3.astro:78).
- **Decorative noise:** All three lean on gradient sludge, backdrop blur, white cards, soft shadows, and polished stock-student imagery. `K2` pushes this hardest, so it reads closest to AI-generated premium theater. See [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:59), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:97), [variant-k3.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k3.astro:79).
- **Proof gaps:** There is some proof, but most of it is late, generic, or floating on stock photos. The imagery is all Pexels-based, which kills anchored proof immediately. The strongest proof is actually in the data: teacher years, A0–B2, visa, hotline, Zalo, named outcomes. The pages do not visually elevate that enough. See [webImages.ts](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/data/webImages.ts:1), [capSoul.ts](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/data/capSoul.ts:31), [capBrief.ts](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/data/capBrief.ts:67).
- **Weak brand-ownable cues:** If the logo disappears, what remains is burgundy/navy, soft cream gradients, rounded cards, and generic education photos. That is weak brand-ownable cues. The French proverb is one of the few ownable moves, but it is buried mid-page instead of defining the visual silhouette. See [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:177), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:213).
- **Variant differentiation risks:** `K2` literally says it is the same core promise with more images. That is route collapse in plain text. `K1`, `K2`, and `K3` could swap most hero assets, stats, teacher cards, outcome cards, and CTA blocks without anyone noticing. See [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:76), [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:51), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:84), [variant-k3.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k3.astro:117).

### What already works
- `K3` has the clearest decision structure and the best audience naming.
- `K1` has the strongest CTA posture with `Zalo trước. Form sau.` and feels less dribbblified than `K2`.
- All three do contain real proof ingredients: hotline, Zalo, named teachers, years of experience, exam names, visa, A0–B2, named student outcomes.

### Highest-leverage changes
1. **Kill the meta copy** — remove every line that talks about what “the homepage”, “the page”, or “K2” is doing and replace it with audience truth, operational detail, or proof. This is the fastest way to stop the AI-generated smell.
2. **Give each route a different decision spine** — stop using the same hero + stats + card-grid rhythm. `K1` should feel like advisory triage, `K2` should feel like real-France journey evidence, `K3` should feel like mobile decision routing.
3. **Swap stock polish for anchored proof** — replace Pexels-heavy imagery with CAP artifacts: real classroom, real Zalo consultation, real student dossier/visa milestone, real roadmap screenshots, real founder/advisor presence.

### Concrete copy edits
- Replace `Một homepage đậm hình ảnh hơn, nhưng vẫn nói đúng tiếng nói của CAP.` with `Cho gia đình đang phân vân giữa học tiếng trước hay chuẩn bị hồ sơ trước, CAP chỉ ra bước nào nên làm ngay và vì sao.`  
- Replace `Một homepage tốt không chỉ đẹp hơn...` with a route-specific claim tied to a user situation, not a design principle.
- Name audience lanes explicitly in `K1` and `K2`: `Mất gốc`, `Cần DELF/TCF`, `Đang chuẩn bị hồ sơ`, `Phụ huynh cần kiểm tra lộ trình cho con`.
- Add proof for `Campus France`, `35+ năm kinh nghiệm`, `14+ năm hồ sơ`, `99% visa`, and named outcomes closer to the hero instead of leaving them downstream.

### Concrete visual edits
- Remove repeated radial-gradient hero backgrounds and most `backdrop-blur` surfaces.
- Reduce the anonymous SaaS card grid rhythm across hero stats, pathways, teachers, and outcomes.
- Increase route-specific visual silhouette:
  `K1`: dossier / checklist / consultation notes.
  `K2`: real-France journey artifacts, not glossy stock collage.
  `K3`: decision-tree / quick-entry / mobile triage blocks.
- Replace stock student imagery from [webImages.ts](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/data/webImages.ts:1) with CAP-native proof imagery from real classes, consultations, results, or a new local asset set.
- Reorder the hero so the eye lands on audience lane first, proof second, action third. Right now it lands on polish first.

### Brand direction test
Describe the revised page in one sentence.  
`CAP helps Vietnamese learners and parents decide whether to start with French, exams, or study-abroad prep by showing the real next step from the learner’s current dossier.`

If that sentence could still describe ten other brands, the direction is not specific enough.

### Verification
- focused checks or tests run  
  Source audit of [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:35), [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:59), [variant-k3.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k3.astro:78), [webImages.ts](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/data/webImages.ts:1), and existing test coverage in [variant-pairing.generic-crap.test.ts](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/tests/variant-pairing.generic-crap.test.ts:1).
- exact result  
  Concrete generic failure modes confirmed: agency/presentation/meta wording in `K1` and especially `K2`; shared template hero structure across all three; stock-image proof gap; current pairing tests only cover `K1` and `K3`, not the full `K1/K2/K3` collapse.
- exact failing or passing evidence  
  `K2` contains `Một homepage đậm hình ảnh hơn` and `Phần này là điểm neo của K2` at [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:69) and [variant-k2.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k2.astro:189). `K1` contains `homepage phải cho thấy` and `Một homepage tốt...` at [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:86) and [variant-k1.astro](/home/cid/projects/iz-design-research/src/pages/variant-k1.astro:195). Existing Vitest cannot run in this workspace because `node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs` is missing from `npm test`.

**Vitest checks to add**

Use one new file, e.g. `tests/homepage-brand-guardrails.test.ts`, and make it cover all three routes, not just `K1`/`K3`.

```ts
import { describe, expect, test } from 'vitest';
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';

const routes = {
  K1: readFileSync('src/pages/variant-k1.astro', 'utf8'),
  K2: readFileSync('src/pages/variant-k2.astro', 'utf8'),
  K3: readFileSync('src/pages/variant-k3.astro', 'utf8'),
};

const metaPhrases = [
  'một homepage',
  'homepage phải',
  'một page',
  'page này',
  'phần này là điểm neo',
  'giữ cho k2',
  'thiên về hình ảnh hơn',
  'một homepage tốt',
];

const requiredAudienceSignals = {
  K1: ['mất gốc', 'chứng chỉ', 'phụ huynh'],
  K2: ['mất gốc', 'du học', 'phụ huynh'],
  K3: ['học tiếng pháp', 'du học pháp', 'cho phụ huynh'],
};

const proofSignals = [
  'zalo',
  'hotline',
  'a0',
  'b2',
  'delf',
  'dalf',
  'tcf',
  'tef',
  'visa',
  'campus france',
  '35+ năm',
  '14+ năm',
  'giảng viên',
  'hồ sơ',
];

const routeOnlySignals = {
  K1: ['zalo trước. form sau.'],
  K2: ['hình ảnh giàu cảm xúc'], // replace later with a better route-specific cue after redesign
  K3: ['lối vào nhanh', 'gửi hồ sơ để cap xem trước'],
};

function lower(s: string) {
  return s.toLowerCase();
}

describe('homepage brand guardrails', () => {
  test('no route ships agency/presentation/meta wording', () => {
    const failures = Object.entries(routes).flatMap(([name, src]) =>
      metaPhrases.filter((p) => lower(src).includes(p)).map((p) => `${name}:${p}`)
    );
    expect(failures).toEqual([]);
  });

  test('each route names concrete audiences instead of a faceless visitor', () => {
    const failures = Object.entries(requiredAudienceSignals).flatMap(([name, terms]) => {
      const src = lower(routes[name as keyof typeof routes]);
      const matches = terms.filter((t) => src.includes(t));
      return matches.length >= 2 ? [] : [`${name} only matched ${matches.join(', ')}`];
    });
    expect(failures).toEqual([]);
  });

  test('each route carries dense proof, not just promise copy', () => {
    const failures = Object.entries(routes).flatMap(([name, src]) => {
      const matches = proofSignals.filter((t) => lower(src).includes(t));
      return matches.length >= 6 ? [] : [`${name} only matched ${matches.length}: ${matches.join(', ')}`];
    });
    expect(failures).toEqual([]);
  });

  test('routes keep distinct voices instead of collapsing', () => {
    const failures = Object.entries(routeOnlySignals).flatMap(([name, terms]) => {
      const src = lower(routes[name as keyof typeof routes]);
      const missing = terms.filter((t) => !src.includes(t));
      return missing.length ? [`${name} missing ${missing.join(', ')}`] : [];
    });
    expect(failures).toEqual([]);
  });

  test('hero imagery is not identical across all three routes', () => {
    const heroKeys = ['mentorSession', 'studyPair', 'studentBooks'];
    const reusedByAll = heroKeys.filter((key) =>
      Object.values(routes).every((src) => src.includes(`webImages.${key}.src`))
    );
    expect(reusedByAll).toEqual([]);
  });
});
```

The key change is not more tests. It is stricter tests on the right things:
- generic filler plus agency/presentation/meta wording
- audience naming by route
- proof density
- three-way route differentiation
- visual route collapse via shared hero imagery and shared source patterns

